CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 10, 1955, pg. 12 reads: "Receptions Climax Wests' 'Golden Year' - Highlights Of The Wests' Receptions - 'Tis seldom that a couple, married fifty years, celebrates the happy occasion with double receptions.  But that was the case when Mr. and Mrs. Thomas L. West Sr. observed their golden year with a home reception at 608 Duff Street on Monday, Sept. 5, and their sons, Thomas L. West Jr. and Raymond, feted them the following night at the north Side Elks.  Snapped during there social events were...Another scene from the Tuesday night reception shows Mrs. Nettie Coleman shaking hands with Mrs. West Sr. as other guests line up to greet the receiving line. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Nettie Coleman shaking hands with Mrs. Thomas L. West Sr., standing next to Thomas L. West Sr. wearing dinner jacket, standing in receiving line in North Side Elks for fiftieth wedding anniversary
